<P>
SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA VOICES / A FORUM FOR COMMUNITY ISSUES: ABOUT THESE PAGES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Voices pages, published Mondays, are intended to reflect the diversity of 
people and opinions in Southern California. Essays, interviews and short 
features explore a range of local and regional issues and opinions.Graphic 
features outline the character of our neighborhoods and the achievements of 
programs and projects of merit.  
</P>
<P>
 How to Participate 
</P>
<P>
 Readers are invited to submit comments and: 
</P>
<P>
 * Questions, complaints and ideas about municipal problems for Gripe, Modest 
Proposal and Getting Answers; 
</P>
<P>
 * Local accomplishments for Making a Difference; 
</P>
<P>
 * Youth column essays, Platform topics, manuscripts for Community Essay and 
clergy names for Sermon. 
</P>
<P>
 Call the Voices automated phone line with brief comments or suggestions: (213) 
237-7670. 
</P>
<P>
 Write 
</P>
<P>
 Voices, Los Angeles Times 
</P>
