<P>
GURU'S COMMUNE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In response to Column One, "A Feud Over Club Meditation," by John-Thor 
Dahlburg, Feb. 5: 
</P>
<P>
 It comes as some surprise that the esoteric topic of whether Osho recommends 
three- or 10-day meditation camps should merit Column One headlines in a city 
known for riot-sized "feuds." Just to set the record straight, those 
disgruntled disciples who complained to your reporter were always free do 
whatever they pleased; they were simply told that if they chose to disregard 
Osho's suggestion, they could not expect the commune to support them by placing 
ads in its newspaper. 
</P>
<P>
 The so-called empire Dahlburg refers to is a projection of his imagination. 
The truth is that of the many hundreds of entities around the world involved in 
Osho's work, every single one of them is economically independent and only 
spiritually affiliated. 
</P>
<P>
 SWAMI PREM AMRITO 
</P>
