Marina, Sr.; Austin Woffinden, Trabuco Hills, Sr.; Nick Ziegler, Huntington 
Beach, Sr. 
</P>
<P>
 League Favorites: Century: Foothill; Empire: Esperanza; Garden Grove: Los 
Amigos; Olympic: Calvary Chapel; Pacific Coast: Laguna Beach; Sea View: Newport 
Harbor; South Coast: San Clemente; Sunset: Huntington Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 1993 Final Poll: 1. Capistrano Valley; 2. Huntington Beach; 3. Esperanza; 4. 
Laguna Beach; 5. Whittier Christian; 6. Irvine; 7. Foothill; 8. Newport Harbor; 
9. La Quinta; 10. San Clemente. 
</P>
<P>
 1994 Preseason Poll: 1. Huntington Beach; 2. Laguna Beach; 3. San Clemente; 4. 
Dana Hills; 5. Newport Harbor; 6. El Toro; 7. Capistrano Valley; 8. Tustin; 9. 
Esperanza; 10. Calvary Chapel. 
</P>
<P>
 Others to watch: Canyon, Corona del Mar, Edison, Foothill, Irvine, La Quinta, 
Valencia, Woodbridge, Whittier Christian. 
</P>
<P>
 Key Dates: Orange County Championships, Marina High, March 11-12; Southern 
Section Playoffs begin May 13. Southern Section finals, all divisions, Cerritos 
College, May 28. 
</P>
<P>
 Notes: The South Coast League figures to be the toughest in the county. Only 
three of the four teams ranked in the top 10 will automatically qualify for the 
playoffs. . . . Coach Mike Jagd returned to El Toro after spending two years 
coaching Colorado's top club team. On March 10, the Chargers will get their 
first severe test, playing at second-ranked Laguna Beach. . . . The Artists and 
the Oilers are heavy favorites to win the Pacific Coast and Sunset leagues. 
Edison and Marina could challenge Huntington Beach, which begins the season 
with a 23-match winning streak. . . . Tustin, Corona del Mar, and Irvine could 
give Newport Harbor fits in the Sea View League if the Sailors don't recover 
quickly from key injuries. "There's not one dominant team in the county, but 
there are six or seven really good teams," Newport Harbor Coach Dan Glenn said. 
"It should be really interesting." 
</P>
