of the county's top outside hitters in Darner, and one of the best middle 
blockers in Hefty. Clem and Hewko are two other college prospects who give Dana 
Hills the core of what could be a championship team. But Simmons has heard it 
before. "We've had the same big guys for four years, but the bottom line is 
that we need to produce," Simmons said. "We have the outside package, but we 
need what's inside . . . the guts." The Orange County championships in March 
should provide a good indication whether the Dolphins will be contenders or 
pretenders this season. 
</P>
