ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: DANA POINT; SMOKEY THE BEAR TO VISIT FOR ARBOR DAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city's annual Arbor Day celebration will be held at Pines Park on Thursday 
from 3 to 5 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The event features several speakers who will discuss environmental 
conservation. 
</P>
<P>
 Other activities include a tree dedication, a workshop on nature and wildlife 
and a visit from Smokey the Bear. 
</P>
<P>
 Participants will get a free seedling and lunch. Awards also will be given for 
a coloring contest. 
</P>
<P>
 The deadline for returning entries to City Hall, 34052 Del Obispo Road, is 
today. 
</P>
<P>
 Pines Park, the site of a recent tree replacement program, is at Camino 
Capistrano, just south of Doheny Place. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 496-4251.FRANK MESSINA 
