<P>
TENNIS ROUNDUP; AGASSI WINS FIRST EVENT IN COMEBACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Andre Agassi, playing in his first tournament in nearly five months, defeated 
Brazil's Luiz Mattar, 6-4, 6-3, Sunday to win the Nuveen Championships at 
Scottsdale, Ariz. 
</P>
<P>
 Agassi, seeded fifth, had been sidelined since Sept. 24 because of a wrist 
injury that required surgery Dec. 20. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the 20th title of Agassi's career and earned him $42,000. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Top-seeded Michael Stich of Germany defeated South African Wayne Ferreira, 
4-6, 6-3, 6-0, to win the Dutch ABN-AMRO tournament at Rotterdam. . . . Thomas 
Muster of Austria won the Mexican Open for the second consecutive year, beating 
Brazil's Roberto Jabali, 6-3, 6-1, at Mexico City. 
