<HEADLINE>
<P>
LADY BLESSINGTON BARELY BEATS SKIMBLE IN BUENA VISTA HANDICAP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL CHRISTINE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Daily Racing Form chart says a nose, but Lady Blessington's victory margin 
was really about a quarter of an inch in the $111,300 Buena Vista Handicap on 
Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Eddie Delahoussaye, who rode Lady Blessington, said he would have been 
satisfied with a dead heat."She ran a winning race, but just got beat by a 
whisker," jockey Corey Nakatani said of Skimble, who has been second six times 
with only one victory in her last 10 starts. 
</P>
<P>
 Skimble finished 1 1/2 lengths ahead of Hero's Love, who was a half-length in 
front of the 13-10 favorite, Possibly Perfect, who lost a couple of shoes in 
the race. Possibly Perfect hadn't run since winning the Yellow Ribbon at Santa 
Anita on Nov. 14. 
</P>
<P>
 Lady Blessington ran a mile on grass in 1:34 4/5 and paid $22.80. This was the 
6-year-old French-bred's 12th victory in 26 starts and her earnings increased 
to $628,992. 
</P>
<P>
 Barry Irwin, president of Team Valor, mapped out this schedule for Lady 
Blessington: the $150,000 Santa Ana Handicap on March 19, breeding to Summer 
Squall and then resume racing, before being sold at a Keeneland breeding-stock 
auction in November. BILL CHRISTINE 
</P>
