<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; WASTEWATCH AWARDS OPEN TO BUSINESSES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 As part of an ongoing effort to encourage businesses to recycle, the city of 
Simi Valley is sponsoring its third annual WasteWatch Awards Program. 
</P>
<P>
 The Simi Valley program is coordinated by the Countywide Recycling Consortium, 
a collection of public and private groups promoting recycling. All businesses, 
schools and nonprofit organizations in Simi Valley are eligible to enter. 
</P>
<P>
 Last year's winners included a tailor who stitched old dresses into new 
outfits, a printer who used recycled paper and a dry cleaning plant that 
recycled cleaning fluids. 
</P>
<P>
 Nomination forms are available through the city's Department of Environmental 
Services at 2929 Tapo Canyon Road, or call 583-6753. Nominations will be 
accepted through March 15. SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</TEXT>
