<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA PAULA; 4 HELD ON SUSPICION OF ARMED ROBBERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Santa Paula police have arrested three men and a 16-year-old boy on suspicion 
of armed robbery after witnesses told investigators that the group had robbed 
two men of a wallet and money, and beaten one of them severely. 
</P>
<P>
 Police responding to a report of men fighting in the 500 block of East Main 
Street about 1:45 a.m. Saturday found two men who had been robbed and beaten by 
the suspects, who later fled, investigators said. 
</P>
<P>
 About an hour later, police spotted a vehicle matching the description of the 
one driven by the suspects and recovered a rifle, the victim's wallet and an 
unspecified amount of cash, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Officers arrested Miguel Angel Zamora, 19; Juan Mendoza Ramirez, 18, and 
Robert Villanueva, 19, all of Santa Paula, and a 16-year-old Santa Paula boy on 
suspicion of armed robbery. 
</P>
<P>
 The three adults were booked at Ventura County Jail, with bail set at $20,000 
each, a jail official said Sunday. Police investigators would not identify the 
victims or provide further details. JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</TEXT>
