<P>
CONCORDIA, SCC FACE ROAD TESTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARTIN BECK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Concordia University and Southern California College men's basketball 
teams will each play on the road Tuesday in the first round of the Golden State 
Athletic Conference Tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Concordia (17-13), seeded fifth, will play at fourth-seeded Point Loma 
Nazarene (13-16), which swept the Eagles in the conference season. SCC (14-16), 
seeded seventh after finishing in last place in conference, plays at 
second-seeded Fresno Pacific (19-10). No. 6 Cal Baptist (13-15) plays at No. 3 
Westmont (16-12). 
</P>
<P>
 The winners advance to the semifinals Saturday at Whittier College. The 
surviving team with the lowest remaining seeding will play No. 1 Azusa Pacific 
(27-3) at 8 p.m. The first semifinal is at 5 p.m. MARTIN BECK 
