<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; ALGERIA; LEADER OF EXTREMIST ALGERIA GROUP SLAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The leader of a Muslim extremist group who was Algeria's most-wanted fugitive 
has been killed in a shootout, security forces announced. Mourad Si Ahmed, head 
of the Armed Islamic Group, and nine of his followers were killed in an assault 
on a building in Algiers, authorities said. Ahmed, who also used the name 
Djafar al Afghani, led the most violent of the Muslim extremist organizations 
that have been waging a two-year insurgency against Algeria's 
military-installed government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
