<P>
BOY, 3, FATALLY HURT WHEN HIT BY TRUCK IN FRONT OF HIS HOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 3-year-old boy was fatally hurt Sunday when hit by a pickup truck as he 
darted into the street in front of his home, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The boy, identified as Derek M. Tolentino, died of head and abdominal 
injuries, police Lt. William C. Stuart said. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident occurred about 3:05 p.m. in front of the boy's home on Demion 
Lane. Stuart said the boy apparently darted from between two parked cars in 
front of his home and into the path of a pickup truck. 
</P>
<P>
 Derek was rushed to UCI Medical Center in Orange, where he underwent emergency 
surgery. But he died about three hours after the accident, Stuart said. 
</P>
<P>
 Stuart said the pickup's driver, identified as 23-year-old Michael T. Newell 
Of Huntington Beach, was not cited and did not appear to be the cause of the 
accident. 
</P>
