<P>
 Woolworth Posts Loss for '93: Woolworth Corp. said it will report 
fourth-quarter and full-year losses because of larger-than-expected charges 
stemming from the proposed sale of its Woolco Canadian discount store division 
to Wal-Mart Stores Inc. Woolworth said it expects to post a loss of $46 million 
for the quarter ended Jan. 29, contrasted with a profit of $165 million in the 
year-ago quarter. For the full year ended Jan. 29, the company had a loss of 
$495 million compared with profits of $280 million in the previous year.Sales 
declined to $9.63 billion from $9.96 billion. Woolworth is restructuring its 
operations to move away from its five-and-dime variety stores and focus more on 
its specialty store chains, such as Foot Locker athletic shoe shops, Champs 
sporting goods centers and Northern Reflections clothing stores. 
