<HEADLINE>
<P>
'I JUST WANT TO SAY ONE WORD TO YOU' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The "plastics" exchange between a middle-aged businessman and Benjamin 
Braddock, a college graduate played by Dustin Hoffman in "The Graduate," the 
top-grossing film of 1968: 
</P>
<P>
 Businessman: I just want to say one word to you, just one word. 
</P>
<P>
 Benjamin: Yes, sir. 
</P>
<P>
 Businessman: Are you listening? 
</P>
<P>
 Benjamin: Yes I am. 
</P>
<P>
 Businessman: Plastics. 
</P>
<P>
 Benjamin (after a long pause): Exactly how do you mean? 
</P>
<P>
 Businessman: There's a great future in plastics. Think about it. Will you 
think about it? 
</P>
<P>
 Benjamin: Yes I will. 
</P>
<P>
 Businessman: 'Nuff said. That's a deal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
